11/10/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Greece wants to settle its unresolved name dispute with Macedonia, Greek Prime Minister and Foreign Minister George Papandreou said on Friday (October 9th) in Istanbul, where he attended a South-East Europe Co-operation Process (SEECP) meeting.
He stressed that Macedonia and Greece share mutual interests.
While in Istanbul, the new PM also met his Turkish counterpart Recep Tayyip Erdogan.
The two discussed bilateral relations, the Cypriot issues, violations of Greek air space by Turkish military planes and perspectives for Turkey's EU membership bid.
(Anadolu news agency, Nafthemporiki, BTA - 09/10/09)
